COVID-19 Hotline - The best way to get answers to your specific questions is by calling your child's school. However, due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, all our students attend classes remotely at this time. Thus, increasing the volume of calls and concerns for families.
If you cannot reach your child's school, please call this toll free number 1-877-708-8195, and someone will get back to you within 24 hours. If you need to contact your child's school or teacher you can also access your school website by using the link below At the school site click contact us and staff directory to email staff. http://edl.io/n1293708

post_text:
CONGRATULATIONS LINCOLN HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT TAMIRA HICKS!
During the week of August 10th-14th, Tamira will be participating in the Harvard Medical School’s teleMED Science Summer Program. Chris L.Gadsden Community Leader

MEDscience teleMED 2020 is an innovative and engaging online program for high school age students. This half-day one-week program will include teleMED patient cases, MEDchats, medical skills workshops, mini-group case studies, and access to the exclusive MEDscience Video Library and Toolbox. Special thanks to Hudson County Freeholder Jerry Walker for helping to coordinate this partnership and Harvard Medical School’s very own Sandra Connors for providing Tamira with this exciting and life changing opportunity.

For those that will not get down to Atlantic City this summer, Riya created a great virtual experience:

Have you heard about Flat Stanley? Well, our P.E. teacher, Mr. Gross has his very own version......

We introduce “FLATTY “G”.

Print him from your computer. Tape him to a paper plate or cardboard. During the month of June, take him everywhere you go. Anytime you play a game, a sport, or workout take a photo of you playing or exercising with FLATTY “G”. Then, send photos to Mr. G via email at agross@jcboe.org He will share your photos to our Facebook pages.

post_text: Ms. Bulger, Math Coach at Dr. Maya Angelou, supported the third grade students from room 247, in creating and making paper airplanes as part of a STEM project. The students read a story, explored designs, created a plan, designed a blueprint and folded a paper airplane to fly. When they met on Google Meet, the students showed Ms. Bulger how they tested their distance. Everyone was excited and proud!

A true display of the power of ART! This gallery represents the ongoing work (from all grade levels) being done remotely by Ms. Pirelli’s art students at PS#38. Their ingenious and creative approaches to these projects is truly evident. Enjoy the collection- from wreaths, to Pop Art Cityscapes, to working with perspective drawings, we thank you for all the support at home for the success of these art projects! Mustang Strong! We hope the art reminds you of the beauty in the world and the talent of our students.
Emma Kelesoglou-1st g. (Cat-composition)
Sanya Singh- 3rd g. (Wreath-found objects)
Shania Sukhai- 4th g. (Pop Art Cityscape)
Brianna Bernal- 4th g. (Underwater Scenery)
Ysabella Marcos- 4th g. (Underwater Scenery)
Aleka Casabuena- 7th g. (Perspective)

The James F. Murray School
May 4 at 9:50 AM ·

Congratulations to Ms. McCarthy's 3rd Grade Class for being selected as finalists in the district's Sustainability STEAM Challenge. The students of Room B2, also known as The Mustang STEAM Team, have made it their mission to use sustainable energy in schools. Under the guidance of Mr. Devito, Mrs. Martinetti, and Mrs. McCarthy, they built and tested a wind turbine that can be installed outside a classroom window. In testing, the turbine successfully charged a battery using only wind power. GO MUSTANGS!

Lincoln High School Athletics - Jersey City, NJ
April 28 at 9:03 AM ·

LINCOLN HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL HONORS 2020: Congrats to both LHS coaches Tommy Best and Bill Zasowski for earning Hudson County coach of the year honors for the 2019-2020 season. Coach Best coached a team with at times seven starters to a consecutive state sectional title and end the season ranked 19th in the state of New Jersey. While Coach Z, has helped Lincoln win at least 20 games for that past three years.

Congrats to our first team Hudson County Boys Lions, Prime Payton and Toriano Munford, with honorable mention to Kelsean McCord and Wendell Moreland. Congrats to our first team Lady Lion Tymira Miller and honorable mention to Tiyanni McClary and Brianna Davis.

This season was so memorable and thank you for making us so proud. #LionNation #LincolnHS #LadyLions #MightyLions

Webb Elementary PS22
April 27 at 9:45 AM ·

Mr. Gross is so excited to share this video with everyone in our PS#22 family and all of J.C.. His friend, Eric has a message for everyone at this time. Eric LeGrand was a top football player at Rutgers U. He was paralyzed in a game back in 2010. I invited him to come speak at MS7. He agreed to come one year to the week of his life changing injury. This was his first visit anywhere other than to the doctor and Rutgers. He was so moved by his experience in JC, he devoted an entire chapter of his book to his visit at our school. Shortly after, CBS sports television came to our school to interview me and some of our students. Our interviews appeared on tv and at the RU football stadium for years. Mr. Gross has always kept in touch with Eric. He now broadcasts football games on tv and radio, does speaking engagements across the country, and won many awards. He is an inspiration to all! We will all get though this tough time. Keep chopping!

Inquiry Hotline

During these rather uncertain times, please know that the entire Special Education Department is partnering with our students, families and staff to insure that every student's educational journey continues. As always, your Child Study Team Case Manager is there to assist you with any questions that you might have regarding your child or loved one's education. In the event that you have a question that you do not know where to direct it to, we have created this email site to assist in forwarding your concerns/ questions to the correct person. Please just click on the following address, and someone will direct your email accordingly.
Again, stay strong and safe,
The Department of Special Education:
SpecialEDMatters@jcboe.org

post_text: The fourth grade students at the Dr. Maya Angelou Elementary School PS #20 are doing virtual field trips to the temple of Isis and to the Great Pyramid of Giza in Egypt. The students are trying to make connections to the weekly story, Seeker of Knowledge: The Man Who Deciphered Egyptian Hieroglyphs written by James Rumford. The students enjoyed the close-up look at the magnificent structures that the Ancient Egyptians have left behind for us to marvel over. The teacher is using the student engagement platform called Nearpod. In this platform, the teacher moves the class through a presentation which allows everyone in the class to interact with the media as they go. For the students who can't attend the live session, they can still have the same experience by completing the student-paced lesson on their own.

PS 28 Christa McAuliffe School
April 16 at 2:43 PM ·

Ready for more Challengers?!

Would bagging the grand prize brighten your day?

Yes it will!!

Our 7th grade team, R.E.M Remote Environmental Monitoring is the NATIONAL GRAND PRIZE WINNER of Lexus Eco Challenge STEM competition❗

R.E.M. team's mission is to make our community safer and more environmentally aware through Remote Environmental Monitoring. The team designed to house and power Environmental IoT sensors or a gateway to help identify air and water quality issues in our community.

Visit @r.e.m. team28 (IG) for T.A.C.O, a covid-19 effort to help our community and beyond.

Congratulations team R.E.M. We can't wait to see more of your work!

We are the Challengers 🚀🌟

🦁💙🦁💙LHS VIRTUALLY SCHOOL PRIDE WEEK
Thank you to Mr. Wally Marte, LHS Physical Education/Health teacher and Volleyball Coach for this sweatshirt. This pandemic has almost cancelled all spring sports. This sweatshirt represents the past two seasons where Lincoln has been public school champs. This also would have been Mr. Marte’s last season coaching volleyball. We have to do something special when we get back to school. We miss school.🦁💙🦁💙
#LHSSpiritWeek #LHSDistantLearning, #LincolnHS, #LionNation
